When $x=0$ is substituted, we find $p(0)=-13r$, but given that $p(0)=-52$, we deduce that $r=4$. Consequently, we derive the expanded form of $p(x)$ as:

\begin{align*}
p(x) &= (x^2-6x+13)(x-4) \\
&= \boxed{x^3-10x^2+37x-52}.
\end{align*}

